# Example monitored-restaurants.txt file
# Copy this file to monitored-restaurants.txt and add your restaurant IDs
# Format: one restaurant ID per line, comments start with #

# TabloCrawler will track all tables created in these restaurants and notify you
# about new tables, participant changes, and table cancellations.

# Example restaurant IDs (replace with actual IDs):
# 12345  # Trattoria da Mario - favorite Italian spot
# 67890  # Osteria del Borgo - great for groups
# 54321  # Pizzeria Napoli

# You can get restaurant IDs from:
# 1. The Tablo app or website (check the URL)
# 2. Using the 'users' command: bun run src/index.ts users --id-ristorante <ID>
# 3. From API responses when scanning tables

# Each line should contain only the numeric restaurant ID
# Lines starting with # are comments and will be ignored
# Empty lines are ignored
# Inline comments are supported: 12345  # My favorite restaurant
